						<div class="postbody">Cool stuff!  Every system needs a Picross game.  Is white-on-black the most relaxing to the eyes, though?  Maybe having pastels surrounding the play grid would be better on the eyes after long playing sessions.<br /><br />You can always borrow some puzzles from my game here:  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.chrismcovell.com/TMLogic.html">http://www.chrismcovell.com/TMLogic.html</a><!-- m --><br />Though I'm not sure what data format you are using.  Anyway, the puzzles I made up (or took from game icons) are not all &quot;Picross-perfect&quot;, ie: solvable without random X-Y guesswork on the rare occasion, like Nintendo's creations are, but hey...<br /><br />Maxim's Picross on the SMS had lots of puzzles that may be able to be borrowed:  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.smspower.org/maxim/SMSSoftware/Picross">http://www.smspower.org/maxim/SMSSoftware/Picross</a><!-- m --></div>

					
